<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1686,1891]" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1722,1747]" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is the first record of this species from 
<collectingCountry box="[806,905,1722,1747]" name="Pakistan" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[916,1162,1722,1747]" class="Insecta" family="Sphingidae" genus="Hippotion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="405" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boerhaviae">
<emphasis box="[916,1162,1722,1747]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">Hippotion boerhaviae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a broad range, from northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[308,406,1758,1783]" name="Pakistan" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, through 
<collectingCountry box="[534,594,1758,1783]" name="India" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[617,741,1758,1783]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[764,834,1758,1783]" name="Nepal" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[856,958,1758,1783]" name="Thailand" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1139,1206,1758,1783]" name="China" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1232,1377,1759,1783]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
and Guangdong), 
<collectingCountry box="[306,404,1794,1819]" name="Vietnam" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, the 
<collectingCountry box="[458,587,1794,1819]" name="Philippines" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[599,708,1794,1819]" name="Indonesia" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
and New 
<collectingCountry box="[826,910,1794,1819]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, to eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1039,1145,1794,1819]" name="Australia" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">Australia</collectingCountry>
, the 
<collectingCountry box="[1199,1387,1794,1819]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,331,1830,1855]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pittaway" box="[352,679,1830,1855]" pageId="12" pageNumber="405" refString="Pittaway, A. R. &amp; Kitching, I. J. (2013) Sphingidae of the Eastern Palaearctic. Available from: http: // tpittaway. tripod. com / china / china. htm (accessed 1 December 2013)" type="journal article" year="2013">
Pittaway &amp; Kitching, 
<number box="[618,679,1831,1855]" pageId="12" pageNumber="405" value="2013.0">2013</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Adults can only be reliably distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[1277,1395,1831,1854]" class="Insecta" family="Sphingidae" genus="Hippotion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="405" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rosetta">
<emphasis box="[1277,1395,1831,1854]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">H. rosetta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by examination of the male genitalia; the larvae are more distinct.
</paragraph>
